In this article, President Donald J. Trump issues a proclamation declaring June 2018 as National Caribbean-American Heritage Month. The proclamation highlights the contributions of Caribbean Americans to the United States, including their impact on the economy, their roles in law enforcement, public service, and education, as well as their achievements in sports. The article also mentions notable individuals with Caribbean roots, such as Dr. William Thornton, who designed the United States Capitol, and Jean Baptiste du Sable, considered the founder of Chicago. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate the history, culture, and achievements of Caribbean Americans through appropriate ceremonies and activities.